    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-08-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-09-10T13:54:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Bad Polluters Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to deny to a Great Lakes Polluter the taxpayer election to expense 50% of the cost of refinery property in the current taxpayer year. Defines &quot;Great Lakes Polluter&quot; as a refinery owner that holds a permit issued by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to discharge a certain level of pollutants into the Great Lakes.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Bad Polluters Act of 2007</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to deny refinery expensing to owners of refineries that are permitted to increase the discharge of pollutants into the Great Lakes.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
